    "summary": "How can we teach as many Dutch pupils from the age of 4 English in the Den Bosch area and beyond? This was my starting point for setting up Such Fun in 2012, a programme for teaching English from Kindergarten and beyond.  Since then teacher trainees and other students from England, the Netherlands and other countries came to Den Bosch to teach at our different schools. Ato-scholenkring adopted the programme and subject teachers of English were added to the teams of students. We also set up a network for all coordinators of English at schools in the area.\n\nThe project now runs in 11 primary schools in Den Bosch and we are teaching over 3600 pupils! Weekly English classes, extra hands activities (teaching small groups of 4 pupils to enhance speaking) and Time for tea (professional development sessions at all the schools by the (non-) native team of the project) made English into a very valuable part of the different schools' curriculum. \n\nThe project has been awarded with the 1st Prize of the European Language Label 2014 and the Orange Carpet Award 2015. \n\nSo far we've worked with Sheffield University, University of Nottingham, Canterbury Christchurch University, University of Hull, Fontys (FLOT and minor of English at PABO), HAN,  Erasmus + and VIOS. ",
